  "texts": [
    "C. Vulnerability Analysis for Traditional Web ApplicationsLLM chatbots are an emerging category of web applications.",
    "Various techniques have been proposed for detecting vulnerabilities or other flaws in web applications [15], [32], [5], [60], [22], [49], [66], [29], [33], [57].",
    "On the one hand, these techniques can be applied to detecting traditional types of vulnerabilities (e.g., SQL injection, XSS) in the web components of LLM chatbots.",
    "On the other hand, these techniques can inspire new approaches for detecting the new types of vulnerabilities (e.g., prompt injection, jailbreak) specific to LLM.",
    "In this paper, the time-based analysis of MASTERKEY draws inspiration from time-based SQL injection attacks."
  ],
